        <body>
            <div type="note" subtype="biographical">
                <head type="title"><persName corresp="#HFB">Henry Fleetwood Backhouse</persName> (<date notBefore="1818" notAfter="1901">1818/19&#x2013;1901</date>)</head>
                <p><persName corresp="#HFB">Backhouse</persName>, the dedicatee of <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="bibliography_of_ruskin_shepherd_note.php"><title type="reference" corresp="#RUSKINBIBLIOGRAPHY" rend="italic">Bibliography of Ruskin</title> (<date notBefore="1878" notAfter="1881">1878&#x2013;81</date>)</ref> by
                    <ref type="note" subtype="biographical" target="shepherd_r_h_note.php"><persName corresp="#RHS">Richard Herne Shepherd</persName></ref>, was an artist and wood engraver. 
                    He was born in <placeName corresp="#LIVERPOOL">Liverpool</placeName> to <persName corresp="#RBRHSMOTHER">Ruth</persName>, 
                    wife of <persName corresp="#TBRHSFATHER">Thomas Backhouse</persName>, whose occupation was a sailmaker, 
                    according to <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#BACKHOUSEBAPTISM">&#x201C;Baptisms at St Peter in the City of Liverpool&#x201D; (Register for <date notBefore="1818" notAfter="1819">1818&#x2013;1819&#x201D;</date>)</ref>, 
                    or a wine merchant, according to the entry in the <title type="dictionary" corresp="#DNB"><hi rend="italic">Dictionary of National Biography</hi></title> 
                    for his wife, the artist <persName corresp="#MBH">Margaret Backhouse</persName>, n&#x00E9;e Holden (<date notBefore="1818" notAfter="1896">1818&#x2013;96</date>). 
                    (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#BACKHOUSEDNB"><persName corresp="#CYELDHAM">Yeldham</persName>, <title type="dictionary_entry" corresp="#BACKHOUSEDNB">&#x201C;Margaret Backhouse&#x201D;)</title></ref>. 
                    One of their daughters, <persName corresp="#MBHDAUGHTER">Mary</persName>, was also an artist. <persName corresp="#HFB">Backhouse</persName> died 
                    in <placeName corresp="#KEW">Kew</placeName>, <placeName corresp="#LONDON">London</placeName>, and was buried in <placeName type="building" corresp="#EASTSHEENCEMETERY">East Sheen and Richmond Cemeteries</placeName> 
                    (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#BACKHOUSEGRAVE">&#x201C;Henry Fleetwood Backhouse&#x201D; [Grave])</ref>)</p>
